In the last lesson, we learned how to work with equivalent fractions. For this

00:00:03.852 --> 00:00:07.680
lesson, we are going to learn how to multiply fractions using chocolate. If I

00:00:07.692 --> 00:00:11.355
have 4 chocolate bars and I want to share them fairly between 2 people, not

00:00:11.367 --> 00:00:15.250
including myself, how much should each person get? You can write your answer

